{"kind":"cas-record-v1","metadata":{"entries":[{"origin_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/cli","target_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/docubot","identifier":"AddDocsOptions.OnlyDocumentImportantIdentifiers","question":"From outside internal/docubot, is there a public API to compute the exact set of undocumented identifiers that AddDocs would target when OnlyDocumentImportantIdentifiers is true, without invoking AddDocs or modifying files?","answer":"No.\n\nFrom the exported API of `internal/docubot`, there is no public helper that computes the exact important-only undocumented target set without running `AddDocs`.\n\nWhat is public:\n- `AddDocs(pkg, AddDocsOptions)` documents and returns diffs, but it may modify files.\n- `AddDocsOptions.OnlyDocumentImportantIdentifiers` enables important-only mode.\n- `NewIdentifiersFromPackage(pkg)` plus `Identifiers` methods can compute general undocumented IDs/counts, and public undocumented counts, but not the important-only subset.\n\nImplementation facts:\n- `AddDocs` dispatches important-only mode to the unexported `addDocsOnlyDocumentImportantIdentifiers` in `important.go`.\n- That path uses unexported helpers:\n  - `importantIdentifiersNeedingDocs`\n  - `importantIdentifiersForPackage`\n  - `totalImportantUndocumented`\n  - `importantScratchExclusions`\n- The important policy itself is also unexported: `importantIdentifierPolicy` and `defaultImportantIdentifierPolicy`.\n\nSo from outside the `docubot` package, you cannot call the exact policy computation. You could only approximate it by reimplementing the private logic, which would be unsupported and could drift.\n\nAlso, if “outside `internal/docubot`” means outside the parent module tree, Go’s `internal` import rules may prevent importing `github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/docubot` at all."}]},"additional_info":{"unix_timestamp":1780593127,"paths":["internal/docubot/SPEC.md","internal/docubot/add_docs.go","internal/docubot/add_docs_test.go","internal/docubot/completion.go","internal/docubot/completion_test.go","internal/docubot/conversation_test.go","internal/docubot/detect_reflow_width.go","internal/docubot/detect_reflow_width_test.go","internal/docubot/doc.go","internal/docubot/find_doc_errors.go","internal/docubot/find_doc_errors_test.go","internal/docubot/fix.go","internal/docubot/fixtures_test.go","internal/docubot/generate_docs.go","internal/docubot/generate_docs_test.go","internal/docubot/identifiers.go","internal/docubot/identifiers_test.go","internal/docubot/important.go","internal/docubot/important_test.go","internal/docubot/improve.go","internal/docubot/improve_test.go","internal/docubot/incorporate_feedback.go","internal/docubot/incorporate_feedback_test.go","internal/docubot/log.go","internal/docubot/partially_document.go","internal/docubot/progress_output_test.go","internal/docubot/prompts.go","internal/docubot/prompts_test.go","internal/docubot/snippets.go","internal/docubot/snippets_test.go","internal/docubot/spec_context.go","internal/docubot/strings_test.go","internal/docubot/target.go"],"git_clean":false,"git_commit":"16bf87f76aa4b7c58f7b3bb1ed1271b523d81d5f","git_merge_base":"68192043cce343842ac710407106317583d1cb09"}}